The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Friday, July 09, 2004 				 Im here, no?
				 	 Shah Rukh Khan																								New Delhi: Hes on sidewalks and billboards, soft drinks and cinema; today Shah Rukh Khan showed up in Parliament, wrapped in a dhoti and in white full sleeves. 																								This was no SRK, but PC. Main hoon na. I am here, the finance minister said, reassuring that reforms were on course, his quicksilver smile making the reference to Shah Rukhs Main Hoon Na obvious. But PC went beyond Bollywood. A reference to Charles Dickens Great Expectations hero Pip followed. My redemption lies in good deeds and not in good words. 
